data.title: Be The Maine Jingle of David and Cindy In The Morning
data.meta_description: Just like your favorite, catchy commercial jingle, we are looking for a David and Cindy in the morning on Q106.5 jingle.
data.text:
We have been inspired by your shares this morning of those catchy commercial jingles that you can't get out of your head. It got us thinking, we would love our very own 'David and Cindy' jingle, or multiple jingles, to air every morning. We know we have a very talented listening audience here in Maine. So, we need YOU.

It does NOT have to be fancy. In fact, all you need is the Q106.5 app on your phone and leave us a "Q VOICEMAIL."

Be as creative, simple, annoying, loud, quiet, seductive, and other adjectives that may or may not describe your style. We just want the wonderfully, inspired you. Hit submit and we will use it on our show, ultimately narrowing it down to our favorite or favorites. Have fun and we can't wait to hear what you come up with!

Here Are Some Maine Commerical Jingles to Inspire You

These were some of our favorites shared this morning on David & Cindy.

Thomas Morelli in Brewer - "You'll wonder where the yellow went, when you brush your teeth with Pepsodent". 1960 TV ad.

Sara Thompson in Brewer - “My bologna has a first name. It’s O.S.C.A.R. My bologna has a second name. It’s M.A.Y.E.R...."

Nick Sutherland in Lincoln - "They've got the sharpest pencil in town, and they just sit around that show room figuring deals and whittling that old pencil down...."

Jenny Lynn Burrill in Maine - "I have a structured settlement, and I need cash now!"

Bri St Peter in Bucksport - "The Harley’s Plumbing and heating song! Cindy can probably verify lol "
